title: Leveraging Compute Power for Drug Discovery
content: My academic weaknesses have always shown themselves through pure sciences such as chemistry and biology. Until recently, I have been ignorant of the plethora of applications where they are used. As a healthy young citizen of a first world country, I have never had to utilize or intake any pharmaceutical drugs other than the occasional Tylenol. However, in today's global pandemic crisis where the cure for COVID-19 is a race against time, I have been able to realize the need for timely and effective drug discovery. Most people never realize the copious amount of money, time and human labor that it takes for a novel drug to be put into production. As a software engineer with a background in machine learning and AI, I have always looked for unconventional applications of my knowledge. One of my goals in academia is to publish a research paper based on AI and machine learning, this technical report is a critical step towards this goal. This technical report is the cumulative effort of the lab reports, design journals and experimental reports that I have written. I am extremely proud of the improvements my technical writing has made throughout these past years and this report is a monument to my ever-expanding technical writing skills.
